CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 30, 1960, pg. 20 reads: "Music Hath Charms - Some of the out-of-town guests at the Frogs' teen-age dancing party got together for a hot minute with the musical instruments of Billy Kimes band during intermission, for this picture. They were encouraged by Morris Fountain, chairman of the event.  Left to right: Mr. Fountain, Carolyn Moore, Washington, D.C.; Linda Wyatt, New York; Muriel Huff, Charleston, S.C.; Garrett Phields, Harrisburg, and Gary Hemphill, Los Angeles, Calif. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Morris Fountain, Carolyn Moore, Linda Wyatt, Muriel Huff, Garrett Phields, and Gary Hemphill, posed around musical instruments in Loendi Club for FROGS teenage dance party
